        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer590275421" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15642063121581276026">Before I share my opinion about this book, I must confess that I did not read the actual writing at first. I listened instead to the audiobook. It is read by Juliet Stevenson, a fantastic British actress. In fact, I found The Brimstone Wedding on Audible as I was looking for recordings by Stevenson. Her rendition of the book is so fantastic that I bought the book afterwards and went through it again. This is the first story by Barbara Vine I took on, so I did not quite know what to expect. I was</span>
  <span id="freeText15642063121581276026" style="display:none">Before I share my opinion about this book, I must confess that I did not read the actual writing at first. I listened instead to the audiobook. It is read by Juliet Stevenson, a fantastic British actress. In fact, I found The Brimstone Wedding on Audible as I was looking for recordings by Stevenson. Her rendition of the book is so fantastic that I bought the book afterwards and went through it again. This is the first story by Barbara Vine I took on, so I did not quite know what to expect. I was pleasantly surprised by the evolving relationship between the two main characters: Stella, a sophisticated, older woman on the verge of death living in a home; and Genevieve, her unsophisticated caregiver. As different in age and social milieu as they are, the two share a deep, devoted companionship and, yes, secrets. I'll say no more or I'll spoil your reading. This is a book that should be read twice to appreciate all the foreshadowing and the intriguing details the author masterfully weaves into the story. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15642063121581276026" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


