<span id="freeTextContainer6975450192844580109">This is a new author for me and I&apos;m torn between a 2 and 3 as a rating. It&apos;s a charming mystery that will appeal to anglophiles &amp; I foresee an addiction to Rendell shortly despite the rating. I won&apos;t classify this as a &quot;beach&quot; read, as this author is so highly enjoyable &amp; readable &amp; perceptive it seems to be more than that. She knows human nature, all right. I see a few similarities with Iris Murdoch who was, I vaguely recall, darker.</span>
  <span id="freeText6975450192844580109" style="display:none">This is a new author for me and I'm torn between a 2 and 3 as a rating. It's a charming mystery that will appeal to anglophiles &amp; I foresee an addiction to Rendell shortly despite the rating. I won't classify this as a "beach" read, as this author is so highly enjoyable &amp; readable &amp; perceptive it seems to be more than that. She knows human nature, all right. I see a few similarities with Iris Murdoch who was, I vaguely recall, darker.</span>
