        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4095571886" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14790648815028460601">This is my first book by Ruth Rendell (writing here as Barbara Vine) and while I was a little wary (not only because she is one of my sister&apos;s favorite authors, but because I wasn&apos;t sure it would be my &quot;thing&quot;) I am so happy to report I really, <i>really</i> enjoyed it!<br/><br/>It was a perfect choice for the sort of book I&apos;ve been craving: heavy on character, beautiful descriptions (especially that of local flora), a bit of intrigue and mystery, and of course, a bit of drama. I would hazard to call this a wond</span>
  <span id="freeText14790648815028460601" style="display:none">This is my first book by Ruth Rendell (writing here as Barbara Vine) and while I was a little wary (not only because she is one of my sister's favorite authors, but because I wasn't sure it would be my "thing") I am so happy to report I really, <i>really</i> enjoyed it!<br /><br />It was a perfect choice for the sort of book I've been craving: heavy on character, beautiful descriptions (especially that of local flora), a bit of intrigue and mystery, and of course, a bit of drama. I would hazard to call this a wonderful summer read, one that you can blow through and easily lose yourself in. Pick this up if you need a break from your usual fare, like I did, and maybe discover a writer you didn't know about (who, luckily, has an extensive bibliography)!</span>
  <a data-text-id="14790648815028460601" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


